<Primary>
<PrimaryPrelims>
<Title><?start-line?>A
<?new-line?>Bill

<?new-line?>To
</Title>
<Number /><LongTitle><?start-line?><Para>
<Text>Require that companies’ remuneration committees have employee <?new-line?>representation; to require that companies hold an annual binding shareholder <?new-line?>vote on executive remuneration; and for connected purposes.<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
</Text>
</Para>
</LongTitle>
<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
<PrimaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>B<SmallCaps>e it enacted</SmallCaps> by the Queen’s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and <?new-line?>consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present <?new-line?>Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:—</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</PrimaryPreamble>
</PrimaryPrelims>
<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00004">
<Title><?start-line?>Employee representation on remuneration committees</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Any public company which has a remuneration committee shall provide that <?new-line?>at least one place on the committee shall be reserved for a person <?new-line?>representative of the employees of that company.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The company may determine whether such persons shall have a vote on the <?new-line?>remuneration committee.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00005">
<Title><?start-line?>Annual binding vote on executive remuneration</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Each public company limited by shares shall, at each annual general meeting, <?new-line?>propose a motion specifying the remuneration of executives employed by the <?new-line?>company, and the result of the vote shall be binding on the company.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>In this section, “executive” means any executive director of the company.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00006">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title, commencement and extent</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Executive Pay and Remuneration Act 2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act shall come into force at the end of the period of two months beginning <?new-line?>on the day on which it is passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act extends to England and Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
